title: In photos: Typhoon Hagibis hits Japan
text:
AP People watch floodwater from the Isuzu river flow by in Ise, Japan, on Saturday, October 12, 2019. In photos: Typhoon Hagibis hits Japan

AP People watch floodwater from the Isuzu river flow by in Ise, Japan, on Saturday, October 12, 2019.

Typhoon Hagibis made landfall in Japan Saturday just before 7 p.m local time on the Izu Peninsula, southwest of Tokyo. The storm has killed at least five people and injured 33, officials said.

The Japanese Meteorological Agency issued a level 5 "Emergency Weather Warning" and at least eight prefectures ordered evacuations totaling more than 930,00 people, according to Japan's Fire and Disaster Management Agency.
description: Typhoon Hagibis made landfall Saturday just before 7 p.m. local time on the Izu Peninsula, southwest of Tokyo, Japan. The storm has killed two people and injured 33.
